The Rotary Club of Mombasa on Saturday recognised and appreciated the Covid-19 frontline health workers at the Pandya Memorial Hospital. They were given tokens of recognition, appreciation and food support that will last them a month. The event was attended by Mombasa Senator Mohammed Faki and RCM president Abdulhamid Aboo. Others present included Pandya Memorial Hospital CEO Rajesh Shukla and Ghafoor Pasta, the chairperson of community service at RCM.